p: Thus, HSD-T was more effective for extraction of geraniol (38.26%) and geranyl tiglate (8.21%) compared to extractions performed by HD (23.07% and 1.97%, respectively) and HSD-P (13.63% and 0.93%, respectively) according to statistical analysis, p < 0.05. Limonene (2.72%) and ( E)-citronellyl tiglate (0.31%) were also identified by HSD-T and were not detected by HD and HSD-P ( Table 1, Figure 1 and Figure 2). The content of limonene in HSD-T is statistically different between HD and HSD-P, p < 0.05.
